The paper presents an auction mechanism for revenue maximization in a specific type of environment, which is a common topic in the field of algorithmic game theory (cs.GT). The mechanism involves sampling and extracting profits, which are techniques commonly used in the design of algorithms for optimization problems (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of a profit extractor, which is a concept from mechanism design and algorithmic game theory (cs.AI). The goal of the mechanism is revenue maximization, which is a central topic in the field of computational economics (cs.EC). Finally, the paper involves the use of biased coins, which is a concept from information theory and cryptography (cs.IT).
